Articles.Content:
When I go to the VAB, there are no items on the list. Also, the loading screen is bugged out. I have tried verifying cache integrity via Steam. [Here's](http://i.imgur.com/HZ1g0RU.png) a screenshot of my GameData. [Here](http://imgur.com/a/pMQMS) are screenshots. [Here's](https://www.dropbox.com/s/tnvoqbd8k5ucxrt/output_log.txt?dl=0) a log.

**Edited <time datetime="2015-07-07T12:21:46Z" title="07/07/2015 12:21  PM" data-short="9 yr">July 7, 2015</time> by Shurikeeen**

There are lots of exceptions in your log. I suspect that several of your mods are not compatible with KSP 1.0.4

    UnityException: Texture 'SXT/Agencies/KDB' is not readable, the texture memory can not be accessed from scripts. You can make the texture readable in the Texture Import Settings.  at (wrapper managed-to-native) UnityEngine.Texture2D:GetPixels (int,int,int,int,int)  at UnityEngine.Texture2D.GetPixels (Int32 miplevel) [0x00000] in :0   at UnityEngine.Texture2D.GetPixels () [0x00000] in :0   at Contracts.Agents.Agent..ctor (System.String name, System.String logoURL, System.String logoScaledURL) [0x00000] in :0   at Contracts.Agents.Agent.LoadAgent (.ConfigNode node) [0x00000] in :0   at Contracts.Agents.AgentList.LoadAgents (.ConfigNode[] nodes) [0x00000] in :0   at Contracts.Agents.AgentList.Start () [0x00000] in :0 

This could be causing all sorts of important initialisation to be missed.

There are lots of errors and exceptions from PlanetFactory. There is a big chunk of exception spam from scatterer.

This looks like the missing part problem:

    FormatException: Input string was not in the correct format  at System.Int32.Parse (System.String s) [0x00000] in :0   at ProtoTechNode..ctor (.ConfigNode node) [0x00000] in :0   at ProtoRDNode..ctor (.ConfigNode node) [0x00000] in :0   at RDTechTree.LoadTechTree (System.String filePath, System.Collections.Generic.List`1 rdNodes) [0x00000] in :0   at RDTechTree.ReLoad () [0x00000] in :0   at RDTechTree.PreLoad () [0x00000] in :0   at RDTechTree.FindTech (System.String requiredTechId) [0x00000] in :0   at PartListCategories.TechTier.ExclusionCriteria (.AvailablePart aP) [0x00000] in :0   at PartCategorizer+. (.AvailablePart ) [0x00000] in :0   at System.Linq.Enumerable.Any[AvailablePart] (IEnumerable`1 source, System.Func`2 predicate) [0x00000] in :0   at PartCategorizer.Setup () [0x00000] in :0   at EventVoid.Fire () [0x00000] in :0   at EditorPanels.ShowPartsList () [0x00000] in :0   at EditorLogic.StartEditor (Boolean isRestart) [0x00000] in :0   at EditorLogic.Start () [0x00000] in :0 

...which looks like a problem with RDTechTree.

I would first make sure that you can repeat the problem with your current setup when you create a new game. Then, either update the mods I mentioned to 1.0.4 compatible versions or remove them and see if the problem is sorted...
